{
  "stem": "24231.1",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We used to have a maid, who was a Jewish girl from, from the eastern part of Romelia, from Czechoslovakia, and she was crying.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And right away, she said she's going to go home and because she can't-- she doesn't know what's going to happen.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So-- and that's-- not long after that, my father-- my uncle lost his business.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He was also a contractor.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And, and the guy, the so-called forvalter, the administrator-- we used to call him Herr Forvalter-- came to our house.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And he said, your, your business and all the equipment will be moved from your house.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "All the trucks and the horses and combined with my uncle's who lived about three miles away from us and had a--",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So they combined the businesses together.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And my father and my uncle, they were advisors to him because this guy didn't know anything about the business, what, what to do.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So they were his advisors.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And, and the guy conducted the business, and so my father didn't do anything after that.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "The Germans came to Prague in March of 1939.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "You were about 10.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "1939?",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Yeah, I think, yes, that's right.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I thought it was '38.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Yeah, '39.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "OK.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "What happened is my-- the uncle who had this business, he had three children.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "His oldest, oldest son, Carl, was, was called for a-- into a transport, with a transport, used to call it AK1, which was an [NON-ENGLISH ] one, which was going to prepare the, the Theresienstadt, which was a-- at this-- this-- Theresienstadt is a town, which is surrounded.",
      "word_count": 48
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was built during the Maria Theresa time.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And it's surrounded by a [INAUDIBLE] wall, so it suited itself for a closed city because the only way you could get out is through some gates.",
      "word_count": 27
    }
  ],
